#. type: Content of: <html><body><h1>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260102-01.en.xhtml:6
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260102-01.en.xhtml:12
msgid ""
"\"The FSFE had the most impactful intervention in the EU’s highest court”"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260102-01.en.xhtml:15
msgid ""
"Our headline quotes a European Commission enforcement officer during a court "
"hearing in a key case where the FSFE is intervening against Apple. As "
"explained below, strategic litigation is one of many actions FSFE takes to "
"protect Free Software. Our goal is simple: empowering people to control "
"technology."
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'alt' of: <html><image>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260102-01.en.xhtml:24
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260102-01.en.xhtml:112
msgid ""
"illustration of a golden cage, from which illustrated birds break free. In "
"the background a EU flag"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260102-01.en.xhtml:28
msgid ""
"Wherever policies, legislation and regulation are being shaped, in meetings, "
"hearings and expert discussions, we are there to make sure that Free "
"Software is not just mentioned, but truly understood and defended. To "
"provide a glimpse of our achievements, just in 2024 and 2025:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><ul><li>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260102-01.en.xhtml:36
msgid ""
"We held 20+ presentations, workshops, talks and panels in Europe and beyond;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><ul><li>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260102-01.en.xhtml:38
msgid ""
"We had 10+ expert meetings with the European Commission, telecom regulators "
"and other authorities;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><ul><li>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260102-01.en.xhtml:40
msgid "We submitted 9 legal and technical reports to policy makers;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><ul><li>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260102-01.en.xhtml:41
msgid ""
"We launched the<a href=\"/activities/deviceneutrality/interop-survey\"> DMA "
"interoperability survey</a> to collect real-world experiences from software "
"developers requesting interoperability from gatekeeper companies like Apple, "
"Google and Microsoft."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260102-01.en.xhtml:49
msgid ""
"This work is effective and far-reaching: some weeks ago, the FSFE <a href=\"/"
"news/2025/news-20251021-01.html\">represented the interests of Free Software "
"developers during the Apple vs European Commission case hearing</a>. This is "
"a pivotal case involving the legality of interoperability. Apple is <a "
"href=\"/news/2025/news-20251015-01.html\">claiming that granting free-of-"
"charge interoperability to developers infringes its “human rights”</a>. We "
"came to the EU’s highest court in Luxembourg to prove them wrong."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260102-01.en.xhtml:59
msgid ""
"Imagine the scene in the courtroom: Apple with more than ten lawyers on one "
"side, and on the other, alone, the FSFE’s lawyer, Dr. Martin Husovec, and me "
"in the audience. With clear and deep expertise, he reminded the Court that "
"innovation does not exempt a company from democratic regulation, and that "
"Apple’s ecosystem is built not only by the company, but also by the "
"developers and users who depend on interoperability and freedom to install "
"software. After the hearing, representatives from the Commission, "
"Parliament, industry and academia approached us to commend our intervention"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260102-01.en.xhtml:70
msgid ""
"However, travelling to meetings and conferences, enabling developers to "
"participate in regulatory discussions, and preparing in-depth legal and "
"technical reports require significant resources. These include practical "
"costs such as travel and accommodation, as well as the time and expertise "
"needed to carry out thorough research and analysis. Two days in Luxembourg "
"exceed 2,000 euros in expenses for our team, and legal work of this scale "
"easily surpasses 10,000 euros."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260102-01.en.xhtml:79
msgid ""
"That is why we need your support! To continue defending Free Software and "
"Device Neutrality where decisions are made."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260102-01.en.xhtml:83
msgid ""
"Your support helps transform expert work into real political impact, and "
"ensures that Free Software voices cannot be ignored. Together, we can secure "
"a Europe where users truly control their devices."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260102-01.en.xhtml:88
msgid ""
"Become a supporter now and contribute to fight for Free Software and Device "
"Neutrality in Europe."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p><fsfe-cd-donate-link>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260102-01.en.xhtml:93
msgid "I want to become an FSFE Supporter!"
msgstr ""

