#. type: Content of: <html><body><h1>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260122-01.en.xhtml:6
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260122-01.en.xhtml:11
msgid ""
"The FSFE at FOSDEM 2026: connect, learn, and celebrate Free Software with us "
"in Brussels!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260122-01.en.xhtml:13
msgid ""
"FOSDEM returns in 2026, once again bringing together thousands of "
"developers, contributors, and Free Software enthusiasts from around the "
"world. Whether this is your first FOSDEM or you are already an expert at "
"navigating the ULB campus, we hope to see you there!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'alt' of: <html><image>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260122-01.en.xhtml:16
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260122-01.en.xhtml:104
msgid ""
"FSFE Booth during FOSDEM 2024: FSFE team and volunteers, male and female, "
"posing behind the FSFE booth full of stickers and info material. One person, "
"male, is also posing before the booth, with one of this arms on the booth "
"table."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260122-01.en.xhtml:20
msgid ""
"On the first weekend of February from Saturday 31 January to Sunday 1 "
"February, the Free Software communities come together and travel from all "
"over the world to attend one of its oldest and most well-known conferences: "
"FOSDEM. Every year, this unique event brings together around 8,000 "
"developers at the ULB Solbosch campus in Brussels."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260122-01.en.xhtml:22
msgid ""
"The FSFE is excited to be part of FOSDEM 2026 with our booth, the <a "
"href=\"https://fosdem.org/2026/schedule/track/legal/\">Legal and Policy "
"DevRoom</a> which we co-organise, and several talks across different tracks. "
"In addition, this year we are also involved in organising two more devrooms: "
"<a href=\"https://fosdem.org/2026/schedule/track/funding-the-foss-ecosystem/"
"\">Funding the Free Software Ecosystem</a>, which debuted last year and <a "
"href=\"https://fosdem.org/2026/schedule/track/foss-on-mobile/\">Free "
"Software Mobile</a>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260122-01.en.xhtml:24
msgid ""
"If you are planning to attend FOSDEM, we encourage you to join our <a "
"href=\"https://matrix.to/#/%23fosdem25:fsfe.org\">Matrix FOSDEM 2026 room</"
"a> to stay up to date and connect with us. In our Matrix room you will also "
"hear all about our social gatherings, which you should not miss!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260122-01.en.xhtml:26
msgid ""
"Like many of you, our team will already be in Brussels on Friday evening. If "
"you would like to kick off your FOSDEM experience with good vibes, we would "
"love for you to join us for our first social meeting! It is a great "
"opportunity to relax, meet fellow community members, and reconnect before "
"the conference begins. All the details will be shared in our <a "
"href=\"https://matrix.to/#/%23fosdem25:fsfe.org\">Matrix room</a>!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><h3>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260122-01.en.xhtml:28
msgid "The FSFE at FOSDEM 2026"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260122-01.en.xhtml:29
msgid ""
"We know how packed these two days will be: countless talks to attend, "
"workshops to learn and improve your skills, and even more people to meet. "
"Still, do not forget to stop by the FSFE <a href=\"https://fosdem.org/2026/"
"news/2025-11-16-accepted-stands/\">booth during FOSDEM</a>! You find us in "
"the K building level 2. Group A - 09."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260122-01.en.xhtml:31
msgid ""
"We will have plenty of goodies waiting for you, including stickers, new T-"
"shirts and socks, hoodies, and much more. You will also find Ada books "
"available in seven different languages, including the new Dutch edition. So "
"come say hello, grab some swag, and have a chat with us at the booth. The "
"FSFE team will be there and happy to meet you, discuss our work, answer your "
"questions, and share more about our activities and our vision for 2048."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><h3>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260122-01.en.xhtml:33
msgid "Saturday, 31 January"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260122-01.en.xhtml:35
msgid ""
"On Saturday, we will have a full day! You will once again find us at the<a "
"href=\"https://fosdem.org/2026/schedule/track/legal/\"> Legal and Policy "
"Issues DevRoom</a>, which we have been co-hosting since 2020. The DevRoom "
"will start at <strong><strong>10:30 (Brussels time)</strong></strong> in "
"<strong><strong>UB5.230</strong></strong> and will feature in-depth "
"discussions on key legal and policy issues affecting Free Software. There "
"you will meet the organizers: Matthias Kirschner (FSFE President) and "
"Alexander Sander (FSFE Senior Policy Consultant), joined by Karen Sandler "
"and Bradley Kuhn (Software Freedom Conservancy), Tom Marble (Informatique, "
"Inc.), and Richard Fontana (Red Hat)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260122-01.en.xhtml:37
msgid ""
"In addition, running in parallel with this DevRoom, two other tracks co-"
"organised by the FSFE will take place. <a href=\"https://fosdem.org/2026/"
"schedule/track/funding-the-foss-ecosystem/\">Funding the FOSS Ecosystem</a> "
"<strong>(UD2.218A)</strong> brings together developers, maintainers, "
"policymakers, entrepreneurs, donors, and funders to explore sustainable "
"funding models that support the long-term health and security of Free "
"Software projects. The <a href=\"https://fosdem.org/2026/schedule/track/foss-"
"on-mobile/\">FOSS on Mobile</a> <strong>(UB4.132)</strong> track focuses on "
"maintaining and strengthening the Free Software mobile ecosystem through "
"research, experimental projects, and new forms of collaboration, fostering "
"innovation while staying true to its core values."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260122-01.en.xhtml:39
msgid ""
"Later on Saturday afternoon, Tobias Diekershoff, FSFE System Hacker and core "
"developer of the <strong><strong>Friendica</strong></strong> project, will "
"<a href=\"https://fosdem.org/2026/schedule/event/DNS7Z8-friendica_-"
"_hidden_in_plain_sight_since_2025/\">give a concise introduction to the "
"project </a>together with Michael Vogel, a core member of the Friendica "
"development team."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260122-01.en.xhtml:41
msgid ""
"Once again, we will round off the day with our community by meeting for "
"dinner and reflecting on the highlights of a long day at FOSDEM. Join us for "
"a relaxed evening of good food and great conversations! Details will be "
"shared in our <a href=\"https://matrix.to/#/%23fosdem25:fsfe.org\">Matrix "
"room</a> 🍽️"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
