msgid ""
"<a href=\"https://fosdem.org/2026/schedule/event/EERURR-"
"implementing_the_cyber_resilience_act_-_engaging_with_open_source/"
"\">Implementing the Cyber Resilience Act - engaging with open source "
"@FOSDEM</a>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><tags><tag>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260224-01.en.xhtml:90
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260302-01.en.xhtml:120
msgid "Norway"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><h1>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260302-01.en.xhtml:6
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260302-01.en.xhtml:11
msgid "Ada’s Norwegian adventure begins!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260302-01.en.xhtml:13
msgid ""
"When Petter discovered “Ada &amp; Zangemann”, he immediately felt the urge "
"to make sure the story was available to the Norwegian speakers.  Now “Ada og "
"Zangemann - En fortelling om programvare, rullebrett og bringebæris” has "
"been published and was presented during the Norwegian local celebrations of "
"the “I Love Free Software Day”. Read Petter’s story!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'alt' of: <html><image>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260302-01.en.xhtml:22
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260302-01.en.xhtml:130
msgid "Ada and Zangemann books in Norwegian"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260302-01.en.xhtml:27
msgid ""
"In November 2023, I first encountered the children’s book <a href=\"https://"
"ada.fsfe.org/\">Ada &amp; Zangemann,</a> written by Matthias Kirschner and "
"illustrated by Sandra Brandstätter. It quickly became clear to me that this "
"was a story I wanted to see available in my native language. That thought "
"led me to get in touch with the author and dive into <a href=\"https://"
"git.fsfe.org/FSFE/ada-zangemann\">the book git repository</a> to figure out "
"what would be required to produce a Norwegian Bokmål edition."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260302-01.en.xhtml:37
msgid ""
"Before I started translating the book, I wanted to change the build process "
"for HTML and PDF editions, in order to simplify the translation process and "
"make it possible to keep track of how the translation corresponds with the "
"original and other languages. I submitted a patch that implemented gettext "
"PO files to maintain translations, creating PO files for existing "
"translations, which was well received. Together with Nico Rikken from the "
"Netherlands we have changed the book building process. It now uses DocBook "
"XML, which is automatically converted to Scribus XML and to HTML for "
"typesetting and website publishing.  This is either done directly or "
"combined with translations in PO format into a translated edition. With this "
"in place, the translator work could finally begin on the translation "
"platform Weblate."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260302-01.en.xhtml:50
msgid ""
"For the actual translating work, I received valuable help from two other "
"volunteers, Hagen Echzell and Henrik G. Sundt. They both assisted with the "
"translation from English and coordinated the Norwegian translation with the "
"German original. Without their help, the book would not have been finished "
"yet."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260302-01.en.xhtml:56
msgid ""
"The translation and the book were actually ready in December, but due to "
"some technical changes required in the final stages to ensure the manuscript "
"met Lulu's distribution requirements, it was not available to a wider "
"audience until after New Year. The result is that I am very happy to "
"announce that the Norwegian Bokmål translation is ready and available for "
"ordering in print via <a href=\"http://www.lulu.com/shop/sandra-brandstätter-"
"and-matthias-kirschner-and-petter-reinholdtsen-and-henrik-g-sund/ada-og-"
"zangemann/paperback/product-zmr289r.html\">lulu.com</a> alongside<a "
"href=\"http://www.hungry.com/~pere/publisher/\"> my other published books</"
"a>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260302-01.en.xhtml:67
msgid ""
"During my conversations with the author, he told me that encouraging readers "
"to buy an extra copy of his book and donate it to their local library had "
"proven to be a very effective approach. It’s an idea that I wholeheartedly "
"support. If you think this book deserves a wider audience, consider ordering "
"an additional copy and donating it to a library that doesn’t yet have it in "
"its collection."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260302-01.en.xhtml:75
msgid ""
"If you choose to do so, I’d appreciate it if you could <a href=\"mailto:"
"%20pere-adazangemann@hungry.com\">email me</a> letting me know which library "
"you plan to donate the book to. This will help me to keep track of which <a "
"href=\"https://git.fsfe.org/pere/ada-zangemann/src/branch/i18n-nb-libraries/"
"LIBRARIES-nb.md\">libraries have already received a copy</a> and make it "
"easier to identify those that still might benefit from one."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260302-01.en.xhtml:83
msgid ""
"<strong>The book was officially launched during the Norway celebrations of "
"the I Love Free Software Day organised by the </strong><a href=\"http://"
"www.nuug.no/\"><strong>Norwegian Unix User Group (NUUG)</strong></a><strong>."
"</strong>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260302-01.en.xhtml:88
msgid ""
"Moreover, NUUG is purchasing around 100 books for organising different "
"events and giving it away at local spots, mainly libraries."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260302-01.en.xhtml:92
msgid ""
"The book's terms of use are Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0 "
"International, which allows everyone to share and modify both raw files and "
"the finished result, as long as all who receive the content can do the same. "
"Any surplus from book sales goes to the FSFE."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260302-01.en.xhtml:97
msgid ""
"My next step will be to see if we can produce more language editions of the "
"book, starting with a Nynorsk edition of Norwegian. The first draft of the "
"Nynorsk translation is ready, but it probably needs quite a lot of "
"proofreading before it is ready for publication. If you are interested in "
"contributing to additional language editions, please have a look at the "
"Weblate project and get in touch with me via email."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p><fsfe-cd-donate-link>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260302-01.en.xhtml:106
msgid "Donate to the FSFE!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><author><name>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260302-01.en.xhtml:114
msgid "Petter"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><h1>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260305-01.en.xhtml:6
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260305-01.en.xhtml:11
msgid "22 events, one message: Maintainers Matter and we love Free Software"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260305-01.en.xhtml:13
msgid ""
"The 2026 edition of “I Love Free Software Day” demonstrated, once again, the "
"strength and gratitude of our Free Software community. 22 celebrations in 12 "
"European countries highlighted the invaluable work of Free Software "
"maintainers as well as bringing people together to thank everyone who "
"contributes to Free Software. Appreciation also extended across the "
"Fediverse, alongside other surprises."
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'alt' of: <html><image>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260305-01.en.xhtml:22
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260305-01.en.xhtml:137
msgid ""
"Collage with I Love️ Free Software text and heart icons. Includes people "
"posing by a heart sculpture, a group gathering, thank you cards, and a comic."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260305-01.en.xhtml:25
msgid ""
"We are really proud of our community and what the Free Software ecosystem is "
"achieving day after day, but there is one special moment each year when we "
"invite everyone to shout it out into the world. “I Love Free Software Day” "
"is our yearly celebration dedicated to saying thank you to all those behind "
"our favourite Free Software projects."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260305-01.en.xhtml:31
msgid ""
"Every year on 14 February, or in the days around it, our communities come "
"together across Europe and online to express their appreciation. Whether "
"through local meet-ups, talks, workshops, postcards, blog posts, social "
"media messages, or simple words of gratitude, the message is clear: Free "
"Software exists and thrives because of the people who build, maintain, "
"document, translate, test, and support it."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260305-01.en.xhtml:39
msgid ""
"For the 2026 celebration, and under the motto “Maintaners Matter”, our "
"communities organised 22 events across 12 different European countries, "
"reaching more than 300 people offline. From cosy café meet-ups to university "
"gatherings and hacker spaces, people came together to say a heartfelt “Thank "
"you” to Free Software maintainers, contributors, and developers."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260305-01.en.xhtml:46
msgid ""
"And many more people celebrated it online. Hundreds of individuals and "
"organisations joined the celebration on the Fediverse, sharing appreciation "
"posts and gratitude messages. The hashtag #ilovefs ranked among the<a "
"href=\"https://mastodon.social/@TrendingHashtags/116069577658470127\"> most "
"used hashtags on the day</a>. For the first time, the celebration also "
"reached the front page of Hacker News, thanks to a “thank you” blog post by "
"Matthias Kirschner, the president of the FSFE, <a href=\"https://k7r.eu/i-"
"love-the-work-of-the-archwiki-maintainers/\">who shared his appreciation for "
"Arch Linux and the extensive ArchWiki</a>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><h3>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260305-01.en.xhtml:58
msgid "New countries, Badges, Fediwall, a comic, and a map"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260305-01.en.xhtml:59
msgid ""
"For the first time, “I Love Free Software Day” reached Croatia and Norway, "
"each hosting a local event and expanding the celebration further north and "
"south across Europe. New cities joined as well, including Bonn (Germany) and "
"Amsterdam (Netherlands). And also Tirana (Albania) returned for this edition."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260305-01.en.xhtml:65
msgid ""
"The Polish community, which reactivated its activities around last year’s “I "
"Love Free Software Day”, strengthened continued its strong engagement with "
"events in Łódź, Warsaw, and Poznań. Poznań hosted one of the largest "
"gatherings in 2026, bringing together nearly 80 participants for a vibrant "
"day of talks, discussions, and shared appreciation."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260305-01.en.xhtml:70
msgid ""
"Across Europe, communities also met in Oxford and the Potteries (UK), "
"Rotterdam, Amsterdam and Eindhoven (Netherlands), Zurich (Switzerland), "
"Barcelona and Madrid (Spain), Frankfurt, Berlin, Bonn and Nuremberg "
"(Germany), as well as in Portugal, where ANSOL organised an online "
"celebration, and many more."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260305-01.en.xhtml:76
msgid "This year also saw remarkable volunteer-driven innovations:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><ul><li>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260305-01.en.xhtml:78
msgid ""
"A new<a href=\"https://fediwall.social/?tags=ilovefs\"> Fediwall system</a> "
"was developed to highlight and visualise online participation across the "
"Fediverse."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><ul><li>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260305-01.en.xhtml:81
msgid ""
"A Polish volunteer set up a<a href=\"https://odznaka.reszka.org/explore\"> "
"BadgeFed instance</a>, creating dedicated “I Love Free Software Day” badges "
"for organisers, participants, and contributors. A creative new way to "
"publicly recognise engagement!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><ul><li>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260305-01.en.xhtml:86
msgid ""
"A long-standing wish for a dedicated event map became reality thanks to Tom, "
"the project leader of mapforge, who made<a href=\"https://mapforge.org/m/"
"11171656?nomenu=true#4.07/46.1/5.8/0/30\"> a customised “I Love Free "
"Software Day</a>” map possible, showcasing celebrations across Europe."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260305-01.en.xhtml:93
msgid ""
"To convey the importance of the day in a more visual and accessible way, the "
"2026 celebrations also introduced a <a href=\"/activities/ilovefs/comic/"
"comic.html\">brand-new comic, explaining why appreciation and recognition "
"for Free Software contributors matter so much.</a>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><figure><a>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260305-01.en.xhtml:101
msgid "<a href=\"/activities/ilovefs/comic/comic.html\">"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'alt' of: <html><body><figure><a><img>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260305-01.en.xhtml:101
msgid "ILoveFS comic by Mullana CC-BY-SA 4.0"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><figure>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260305-01.en.xhtml:101
msgid "</a>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><figure><figcaption>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260305-01.en.xhtml:102
msgid ""
"Comic by <a href=\"https://mullana.de/creative-commons/\">Mullana under CC-"
"BY-SA 4.0</a> ❤"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260305-01.en.xhtml:105
msgid ""
"For the 2026 edition, the Software Freedom Podcast released its 47th "
"episode, “ILoveFS: Let’s meet our maintainers”. In this episode, Bonnie "
"Mehring speaks with maintainer Lorenz Kästle about the rewards and "
"challenges of maintaining Free Software projects in one’s free time."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260305-01.en.xhtml:111
msgid ""
"“I Love Free Software Day” has grown into a well-established online and "
"offline celebration of Software Freedom. Above all, the day remains what it "
"has always been: a joyful celebration full of gratitude, connection, and "
"recognition."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260305-01.en.xhtml:116
msgid ""
"To everyone who organised an event, sent a postcard, shared a hashtag, "
"joined a podcast, created a badge, developed tools, or simply said "
"<strong>“Thank you”: thank you for making “I Love Free Software Day 2026: "
"Maintainers Matter” such a special and inspiring celebration.</strong>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260305-01.en.xhtml:122
msgid ""
"Wanna know more? Read our <a href=\"/activities/ilovefs/report/"
"report_2026.html\">Report about the 2026 I love Free Software day "
"celebrations</a>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><tags><tag>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260305-01.en.xhtml:129
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260406-01.en.xhtml:299
msgid "I Love Free Software Day"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><h1>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260316-01.en.xhtml:6
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260316-01.en.xhtml:11
msgid "450 FSFE supporters affected: Payment provider Nexi cancelled us"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260316-01.en.xhtml:14
msgid ""
"Our long-term payment provider Nexi has terminated our contract without "
"prior notice. As a result, our supporters’ recurring credit card and direct "
"debit donations have been halted by them. This affects more than 450 FSFE "
"supporters, whom we have already informed by email."
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'alt' of: <html><image>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260316-01.en.xhtml:17
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260316-01.en.xhtml:44
msgid ""
"A person holds a credit card while using a laptop for an online transaction. "
"A bold red banner with the word “cancelled” is overlaid across the image, "
"indicating the payment or card has been blocked."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260316-01.en.xhtml:20
msgid ""
"<strong>If you are donating by direct debit, or if you have set up a "
"recurring donation by credit card before 18 November 2025, you are affected "
"by this. If in those cases, you did not receive an email from us, please "
"contact us so that you can continue supporting us for software freedom.</"
"strong>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260316-01.en.xhtml:22
msgid ""
"Over the past few months, our former payment provider Nexi S.p.A. (“Nexi”) "
"requested access to private data, which we understood to be specifically the "
"usernames and passwords of our supporters. We have refused this request. All "
"our attempts to clarify Nexi’s request, or to understand how their need for "
"such information was necessary and legal, were met with what we consider to "
"be vague and unsatisfactory explanations relating to a general need for risk "
"analysis."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260316-01.en.xhtml:24
msgid ""
"Subsequently, we found ourselves unable to receive credit card donations "
"through Nexi’s system. In the afternoon of 10 March, we were further "
"informed that our contract had been cancelled a few days prior on 7 March, "
"due to our supposed failure to meet their deadline to fulfil their request. "
"This deadline was not communicated to us beforehand, despite us having been "
"Nexi’s customer for the past 15 years."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260316-01.en.xhtml:26
msgid ""
"More than 450 current FSFE supporters who use automatic renewal with credit "
"card or direct debit have been affected by Nexi’s actions. While we have "
"already prepared a transition to a new payment provider, existing supporter "
"accounts cannot be migrated automatically."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260316-01.en.xhtml:28
msgid ""
"From previous experience, we know there are always some people who might not "
"read our email. If we lose their financial support because of this "
"unforeseen hurdle, this will affect our work for Free Software."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260316-01.en.xhtml:30
msgid ""
"The decisions that Nexi has made are incomprehensible to us. Over the last "
"months, as part of a security audit that Nexi claimed to be conducting, we "
"have provided them with large amounts of the FSFE’s financial documentation, "
"which even included private information of our executive staff. We have "
"answered all of their questions. But we have to draw a line when private "
"companies like Nexi demand access to the sensitive and private data of our "
"supporters."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260316-01.en.xhtml:32
msgid ""
"<strong>On our website, all <a href=\"/donate\">donate pages</a> have been "
"updated already and include our new payment provider. Especially in this "
"difficult situation, we highly appreciate your <a href=\"/donate\">support</"
"a> for software freedom.</strong>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><version>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260406-01.en.xhtml:3
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202601.en.xhtml:3 fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202602.en.xhtml:3
msgid "2"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><h1>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260406-01.en.xhtml:6
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260406-01.en.xhtml:11
msgid "How we celebrate \"I Love Free Software Day\" in Poznań, Poland"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260406-01.en.xhtml:13
msgid ""
"Not so long ago, the Free Software community celebrated the \"I Love Free "
"Software Day\". A day in which the FSFE, our volunteers and many other "
"organisations and individuals thank all contributors for their commitment to "
"use, study, share and improve Free Software. Without them there is no "
"software freedom!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'alt' of: <html><image>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260406-01.en.xhtml:21
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260406-01.en.xhtml:306
msgid ""
"A red heart with ones and zeros in a white background also consisting of "
"ones and zeros."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260406-01.en.xhtml:25
msgid ""
"For the \"I Love Free Software Day\" in 2026, 22 events were organised <a "
"href=\"/activities/ilovefs/report/report_2026.html\">across 12 European "
"countries</a>. Several of them were organised by the <a href=\"/about/"
"groups.html\">FSFE's local groups</a>.  At these celebrations people came "
"together to share their knowledge and stories about Free Software, discuss "
"and inspire others to study, use, improve and share the software we all "
"love. Each of these celebrations is unique and showcases the commitment of "
"our community, from local gatherings with pizza and fun Free Software games "
"to larger events addressing new people with talks and networking."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260406-01.en.xhtml:38
msgid ""
"The biggest <a href=\"https://ilovefs.org\">\"I Love Free Software\"</a> "
"event in our 2026 celebrations took place in Poznań (Poland) with around 80 "
"participants. The event was organised by the local FSFE group with the "
"collaboration of their local university. Here, they were allowed to use a "
"lecture hall for presentations and they also had some time to network "
"afterwards."
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'alt' of: <html><body><figure><img>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260406-01.en.xhtml:45
msgid "People sitting in a lecture hall and listening to a presentation."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><figure><figcaption>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260406-01.en.xhtml:46
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260406-01.en.xhtml:132
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260406-01.en.xhtml:240
msgid "\"I Love Free Software Day\" celebrations in Poznań, 2026."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260406-01.en.xhtml:49
msgid ""
"One of the main organisers of the event was Paweł Wiczyński, also known as "
"‘pomidor’. Paweł, is a founding member of <a href=\"https://hspoz.pl/"
"\">Knyfyrtel Poznan Hackerspace</a>, and he has been a Free Software "
"enthusiast for a very long time. The first time he got in touch with Free "
"Software was when he was very young, just about 10 years old. At that age he "
"heard about GNU/Linux, a Free Software alternative to Windows, and tried it "
"out on his computer. From there onwards he has been hooked and learned more "
"and more about the FLOSS ecosystem."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260406-01.en.xhtml:65
msgid ""
"<strong>FSFE</strong>: Hello Paweł, thank you so much for finding time to do "
"this interview. Let's start by getting back to the roots, why do you believe "
"Free Software is important?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260406-01.en.xhtml:73
msgid ""
"<strong>Paweł, one of the FSFE Poznań coordinators</strong>: I think that "
"Free Software is important because it allows people to keep control over the "
"technology they use. Today, our lives are increasingly dependent on various "
"types of software. We use it every day on many different devices. If we do "
"not ensure that this software is free, we allow entities, such governments, "
"companies or corporations, to control us. This is why I believe that Free "
"Software should be promoted and used wherever possible."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260406-01.en.xhtml:87
msgid ""
"<strong>FSFE</strong>: How did you first hear of the “I Love Free Software "
"Day”? And what were your thoughts about this initiative?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260406-01.en.xhtml:93
msgid ""
"<strong>Paweł</strong>: My colleague Damian, who is the FSFE coordinator in "
"Poland, told me about the \"I Love Free Software Day\" initiative. I had not "
"heard of this day before. I really liked it and thought it would be great to "
"join in. As a member of Knyfyrtel Poznan Hackerspace, I enjoy organizing "
"events for the community. And this was a great idea to do something new that "
"fits in with our mission."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260406-01.en.xhtml:100
msgid ""
"I very like that the event is organized in many places across numerous "
"cities in Europe. I believe that such initiatives are truly needed, because "
"they make it possible to reach a much wider audience. By acting together on "
"an international scale, we can amplify the message and show that the Free "
"Software community is strong, connected, and active beyond local borders."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260406-01.en.xhtml:112
msgid ""
"<strong>FSFE</strong>:Why did you decide to organise an “I Love Free "
"Software Day” event in 2026?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260406-01.en.xhtml:117
msgid ""
"<strong>Paweł</strong>: We were inspired to organise this year's “I Love "
"Free Software Day” by the success of last year's edition and the enthusiasm "
"of the community. We had enough willing organisers to hold a large meetup "
"for the community."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260406-01.en.xhtml:122
msgid ""
"Moreover, we have very good connections with the academic community in "
"Poznań. We wanted to use it to reach not only students, but also IT "
"professionals, enthusiasts, and regular users interested in Free Software. "
"Our goal was simply to bring these groups together in one place and give "
"them an opportunity to learn something new, network, and get involved in "
"Free Software initiatives."
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'alt' of: <html><body><figure><img>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260406-01.en.xhtml:131
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260406-01.en.xhtml:239
msgid ""
"People sitting in a lecutre hall and one person is up front presenting a "
"presentation."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260406-01.en.xhtml:137
msgid ""
"<strong>FSFE</strong>: This was the second time you organised the local "
"celebration in Poznań. How was the event in 2026 compared to the event in "
"2025?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260406-01.en.xhtml:143
msgid ""
"<strong>Paweł</strong>: That’s right. We organised “I Love Free Software "
"Day” for the first time last year, and we had no idea how many participants "
"to expect. The reality exceeded our expectations – there were about 50 "
"people, and they almost did not fit in the room."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260406-01.en.xhtml:148
msgid ""
"This year, the event was even bigger – there was more pizza, more speakers, "
"and more participants. Around 80 people attended, and this time we made sure "
"to book a larger room. We also carefully planned the schedule to avoid "
"delays, including an extra break for networking and socialising. "
"Additionally, we organised a campaign to write cards to Free Software "
"creators and maintainers."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260406-01.en.xhtml:158
msgid ""
"<strong>FSFE</strong>: And in general, how was the 2026 celebration of the "
"“I Love Free Software Day”?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260406-01.en.xhtml:162
msgid ""
"<strong>Paweł</strong>: We organised the in the form of a meetup at Poznań "
"University of Technology – short 15-minute talks with additional Q &amp; A "
"from participants. A total of six speakers talked about various FLOSS "
"projects and how they use it in their daily work. After that, there was time "
"for networking and refreshments with pizza and drinks. Overall, the event "
"was very successful – we received positive feedback from the community, made "
"new contacts and exchanged knowledge."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260406-01.en.xhtml:173
msgid ""
"<strong>FSFE</strong>: How did you start the cooperation with the University?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260406-01.en.xhtml:178
msgid ""
"<strong>Paweł</strong>: As Knyfyrtel Poznan Hackerspace, we already had the "
"opportunity to organise events in cooperation with scientific clubs at "
"Poznań University of Technology. For “I Love Free Software Day,” we "
"leveraged these connections and invited them to collaborate."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260406-01.en.xhtml:182
msgid ""
"Last year, our main co-organiser was <a href=\"https://"
"putrequest.put.poznan.pl/\">PUTrequest_ team</a>, while this year it was <a "
"href=\"https://lag.edu.pl/\">Linux Academic Group</a>. They handled all the "
"formalities, secured the venue, and arranged support from the university "
"authorities. We really appreciate working with the academic community and "
"look forward to building even more joint initiatives in the future."
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'alt' of: <html><body><figure><img>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260406-01.en.xhtml:190
msgid "Picture of a person with a microphone in their hand and talking."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260406-01.en.xhtml:195
msgid ""
"<strong>FSFE</strong>: Did you use any of the materials the FSFE provides "
"for organising a local celebration?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260406-01.en.xhtml:201
msgid ""
"<strong>Paweł</strong>: We had a lot of materials from last year – stickers, "
"posters, cards, and leaflets. We also printed some of the stickers "
"ourselves. Presentation templates used during the opening and closing of the "
"event were very helpful. It would surely be easier if package arrived, but "
"this year we managed without it."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260406-01.en.xhtml:212
msgid ""
"<strong>FSFE</strong>: What would you recommend to others when they want to "
"organise an “I Love Free Software Day” celebrations and what are pitfalls "
"you would say should be avoided?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260406-01.en.xhtml:217
msgid ""
"<strong>Paweł</strong>: First and foremost, do not hesitate, just do it! All "
"you need is a venue and motivation. If possible, collaborate with local "
"groups, students, and academic circles, as they can help you attract "
"participants. Take care of promotion – use social media, event aggregators, "
"chats, and online groups to advertise your event. Tell your friends to tell "
"their friends. You can also create a dedicated website and put up posters in "
"the neighbourhood."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260406-01.en.xhtml:223
msgid ""
"As for pitfalls, if you are organising an event at a university, be prepared "
"for delays with formalities and permits – handling these can take much more "
"time than expected. Also, make sure to order promotional materials well in "
"advance; in our case, one month was not enough. Planning these details early "
"will save a lot of headaches and help the event run smoothly."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260406-01.en.xhtml:231
msgid ""
"<strong>FSFE</strong>: Thank you for sharing your very hands-on advice! Just "
"a quick follow-up here, how many people are involved in organising the event?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260406-01.en.xhtml:236
msgid ""
"<strong>Paweł</strong>: There were about 20 people who took part in the "
"organisational meetings."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260406-01.en.xhtml:245
msgid ""
"<strong>FSFE</strong>: Do you also organise additional events throughout the "
"year and what would be the next meeting where others can join you?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260406-01.en.xhtml:250
msgid ""
"<strong>Paweł</strong>: Yes. We organise many different events, but our "
"biggest one is <a href=\"https://piwo.sh/\">P.I.W.O. – Poznań Free Software "
"Fest</a>\".  It is a free conference that we organise in cooperation with "
"the academic community in Poznań. It has over 20 years of tradition, but it "
"was inactive for over 7 years. The Knyfyrtel Poznan Hackerspace reactivated "
"it last year – and it was a great success.  Almost 200 participants, 2 "
"tracks, free pizza, LAN Party and lightning talks. This year, we are "
"planning another edition on an even larger scale. This year, it will be on "
"30 May 2026 at the Faculty of Mathematics and Computer Science, AMU in "
"Poznań (<a href=\"https://piwo.sh/en/\">English website</a> and <a "
"href=\"https://fosstodon.org/@piwo\">social media</a>)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260406-01.en.xhtml:264
msgid ""
"<strong>FSFE</strong>: Is there a Free Software project, which you would "
"like to highlight and say ‘Thank you’ to?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260406-01.en.xhtml:270
msgid ""
"<strong>Paweł</strong>: There are many Free Software projects that I use and "
"would like to thank.  But if I had to choose one, it would be Thunderbird. "
"It is my favourite email client. I have been using it for years. And "
"recently, it has been developing very dynamically. I really appreciate the "
"Thunderbird team and wish them continued success and growth with the project."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260406-01.en.xhtml:278
msgid ""
"<strong>FSFE</strong>: Paweł, thank you very much for your time! I hope "
"there will be many more “I Love Free Software Day” celebrations in Poznań."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><sidebar>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260406-01.en.xhtml:288
msgid ""
"<cite><a href=\"https://ilovefs.org/\"><strong>I Love Free Software Day "
"2026</strong></a> will be happening on the 14th of February.  On this day we "
"will highlight the importance of all Free Software contributors. Join us and "
"create your own event!</cite>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><tags><tag>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260406-01.en.xhtml:297
msgid "Interview"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><tags><tag>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260406-01.en.xhtml:300
msgid "Poland"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><h1>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260420-01.en.xhtml:6
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260420-01.en.xhtml:11
msgid "Apple keeps challenging its interoperability obligations under the DMA"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260420-01.en.xhtml:13
msgid ""
"A new FSFE report exposes how 56 interoperability requests under the Digital "
"Markets Act have produced no concrete solutions by Apple, and how their "
"declines contradict their own official documentation, leaving third-party "
"developers locked out of iOS and iPadOS, despite European Commission’s "
"latest specification decision."
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'alt' of: <html><image>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260420-01.en.xhtml:19
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260420-01.en.xhtml:312
msgid ""
"Ilustration showing what looks like a snake in the shape of an apple in "
"black with a red shadow"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><figure><figcaption>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260420-01.en.xhtml:20
msgid ""
"CC-BY-SA 4.0. by <a href=\"https://rahak.net/work.html\">Rahak</a> for FSFE."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260420-01.en.xhtml:23
msgid ""
"The Free Software Foundation Europe (FSFE)’s report <a href=\"https://"
"download.fsfe.org/campaigns/device-neutrality/FSFE-DMA-AppleReport-"
"v1.pdf\">“The challenges of regulating interoperability. Analysing Apple’s "
"request-based approach under the Digital Markets Act”</a> sheds lights on "
"how Apple has been implementing the interoperability obligations under the "
"<a href=\"/activities/dma\">Digital Markets Act (DMA)</a>.  Under the "
"European Commission (EC)'s latest rules, third-party developers can formally "
"request access to Apple's platform. This report looks at how Apple has "
"handled those requests in practice. The evidence of the report is based on "
"public data from Apple’s public tracker, implemented as a requirement of the "
"regulatory framework."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260420-01.en.xhtml:35
msgid ""
"Despite the EC's clear requirements under the Digital Markets Act, the "
"FSFE's report finds that, as of 22 March 2026, not one of 56 formal "
"interoperability requests has resulted in a solution. Developers requesting "
"access to Just-in-Time compilation, NFC protocols, and Bluetooth Low Energy "
"Audio, for example, have seen their requests denied often because the "
"features in question “fall outside of the scope of the law”. Despite the "
"company's own technical documentation, which points in the opposite "
"direction. The report elaborates on the shortcomings of Apple's request-"
"based approach in relation to effective interoperability: Apple’s model "
"requires developers to navigate account creation, fees, detailed requests, "
"internal review, and potentially long implementation timelines, fearing "
"sudden and unreasoned closure of their developer accounts during the whole "
"process."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260420-01.en.xhtml:50
msgid ""
"The report argues that while the regulatory framework issued by the EC on "
"interoperability represents a progress, requiring transparency and due "
"process obligations from Apple, governance issues, as pointed out, will "
"arise in the future. Therefore, the report calls for open standards, "
"transparent procedures, and stronger regulatory enforcement so that Free "
"Software developers can participate on fairer terms within the mobile "
"ecosystem."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><blockquote>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260420-01.en.xhtml:58
msgid ""
"“Despite being legally required by the European Commission, Apple continues "
"to obstruct effective interoperability. Out of 56 requests, not a single one "
"has resulted in a new interoperability solution. Developers are denied "
"access to Just-In-Time-Compilation, NFC, or Bluetooth Low Energy Audio with "
"arguments contradicting Apple’s own documentation. And there is the constant "
"fear for developers to lose their developer accounts. The DMA must be "
"implemented in a developer-friendly way, ensuring that legal obligations "
"translate into fair and equal access to iOS and iPadOS "
"features.”<cite>Matthias Kirschner, FSFE President</cite>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><blockquote>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260420-01.en.xhtml:71
msgid ""
"“Interoperability only works when it is built into the platform from the "
"start. The European Commission’s regulatory framework to facilitate "
"interoperability between Apple and competitors is a good step forward. Or "
"report sheds lights on the challenges faced by software developers under "
"this new framework.”<cite>Lucas Lasota, FSFE Legal Programme Manager</cite>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260420-01.en.xhtml:80
msgid ""
"You can read the full report <a href=\"https://download.fsfe.org/campaigns/"
"device-neutrality/FSFE-DMA-AppleReport-v1.pdf\">here</a>.  What follows is a "
"summary of the main findings."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p><fsfe-cd-donate-link>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260420-01.en.xhtml:87
msgid "I want to donate for Device Neutrality!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><h3>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260420-01.en.xhtml:91
msgid "Recap on DMA interoperability"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260420-01.en.xhtml:93
msgid ""
"Apple is one of the largest tech companies in the world. Due to its market "
"power, it is designated in Europe as a gatekeeper under the DMA, a law "
"designed to regulate digital competition and open closed platforms. Under "
"this legislation, Apple must provide free-of-charge interoperability for the "
"features and functionalities controlled by its mobile operating systems, iOS "
"and iPadOS. This should allow users to install and remove apps freely, use "
"alternative app stores, and enable developers to connect their apps to key "
"software and hardware features without being blocked."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260420-01.en.xhtml:103
msgid ""
"Making Article 6(7) of the DMA Free-Software-developer friendly is crucial "
"for <a href=\"/activities/deviceneutrality.index.html\">Device Neutrality</"
"a>: it obliges gatekeepers to provide effective and free of charge "
"interoperability with, and access to, the software and hardware features of "
"designated operating systems such as iOS and iPadOS. In practical terms, "
"this means that developers must be able to access the same operating-system-"
"controlled features that the gatekeeper’s own services use, instead of being "
"kept on the outside looking in."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260420-01.en.xhtml:112
msgid ""
"The DMA represents an opportunity for Free Software developers to compete on "
"equal terms with gatekeeper services. Free Software developers deserve the "
"right to build genuine alternatives to closed ecosystems like iOS and "
"iPadOS, while users gain access to alternative app stores, payment systems, "
"and unfettered software installation in mobile devices as well."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><h3>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260420-01.en.xhtml:119
msgid "Apple DMA interoperability compliance in practice"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260420-01.en.xhtml:121
msgid ""
"When the DMA took effect, it expected gatekeepers like Apple to deliver "
"interoperability by default: publishing APIs, clear documentation, and "
"technical access matching that are equivalent to those used for their own "
"services. Instead, Apple created a request-based system where each developer "
"must seek permission for specific features, waiting for Apple to decide if "
"they are ”in scope”.  This led the European Commission to launch a "
"specification case (<a href=\"https://competition-cases.ec.europa.eu/cases/"
"DMA.100204\">DMA.100204</a>), requiring a fairer process with timelines and "
"a <a href=\"https://developer.apple.com/file/?file=interoperability-request-"
"tracker\">public tracker</a> (for access to which an Apple account is "
"required)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><h3>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260420-01.en.xhtml:134
msgid "How a developer must request interoperability to Apple"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260420-01.en.xhtml:136
msgid ""
"Rather than opening its platform by publishing APIs and documentation from "
"the outset, Apple built a request-based system in which every developer must "
"apply for access to each feature they need."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260420-01.en.xhtml:141
msgid ""
"The process starts with an Apple developer account, which costs at least 99 "
"USD (in Spring 2026), then developers need to fill a detailed request "
"describing the feature, the use case, the technical need, and possible "
"alternatives to the feature or functionality they are asking access for. "
"Apple then performs an initial eligibility check within 20 working days, "
"after which it may proceed, reject the request, or say that an existing "
"solution already covers it."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260420-01.en.xhtml:149
msgid ""
"If Apple rejects the request, developers can seek internal review and, in "
"some cases, conciliation. Even when a request is accepted, Apple can still "
"take up to 24 months to implement the result, depending on its own "
"assessment of technical complexity. That means the process can stretch "
"across months or years before developers see any practical benefit, even "
"though the underlying right to interoperability is already supposed to exist."
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'alt' of: <html><body><figure><img>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260420-01.en.xhtml:159
msgid "flowchart describing the interoperability process"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><figure><figcaption>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260420-01.en.xhtml:161
msgid ""
"Timeline proposed by the European Commission to regulate Apple’s "
"interoperability requests. Source: European Commission."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260420-01.en.xhtml:166
msgid ""
"The EC’s intervention gave the process a regulatory framework. As of March "
"22, 2026, Apple has received 56 interoperability requests under Article 6(7) "
"of the DMA since May 2025, of which 43 have been closed, but 27 of those "
"closures are fully confidential. Of the 16 publicly disclosed closures, none "
"resulted in Apple developing a new interoperability solution: 10 were denied "
"on “technical grounds”, 2 were dismissed by Apple citing “existing "
"solutions”, and 3 were rejected as “out of scope or invalid”."
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'alt' of: <html><body><figure><img>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260420-01.en.xhtml:178
msgid ""
"chart showing the interoperability requests received by Apple under Art. "
"6(7) DMA until 22.03.2026"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><figure><figcaption>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260420-01.en.xhtml:180
msgid ""
"Interoperability requests received by Apple under Article 6(7) DMA until "
"22.03.2026"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'alt' of: <html><body><figure><img>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260420-01.en.xhtml:186
msgid ""
"chart showing the status of the interoperability requests received by Apple "
"under Art. 6(7) DMA until 22.03.2026"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><figure><figcaption>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260420-01.en.xhtml:188
msgid ""
"Status of the interoperability requests received by Apple under Article 6(7) "
"DMA until 22.03.2026"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><h3>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260420-01.en.xhtml:192
msgid "What Apple tracker reveals: four examples of rejected requests"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260420-01.en.xhtml:194
msgid ""
"Several individual cases illustrate how the process works in practice. A "
"Free Software terminal-like app requested access to Just-In-Time (JIT) "
"compilation. JIT is already used by Apple’s Safari browser to run downloaded "
"code securely in a sandbox. But Apple rejected the request from the "
"developer and said JIT for non-browser apps was not a feature controlled by "
"iOS."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260420-01.en.xhtml:201
msgid ""
"Another developer sought access to FIDO tokens in wallet passes and the VAS "
"NFC protocol used by Apple Wallet. Apple again denied that these were OS-"
"controlled features, despite its own documentation requiring a special "
"entitlement for NFC access."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260420-01.en.xhtml:206
msgid ""
"A third case involved Bluetooth LE Audio for specialised research hardware. "
"Apple said the feature was not available to or used by Apple’s own hardware "
"or services, even though Bluetooth Low Energy is part of iOS and comparable "
"functionality exists on competing platforms.  Two further requests sought "
"alternatives to Apple’s Push Notification Service, including decentralised "
"or user-controlled notification servers. But both were rejected on the "
"grounds that APNS is already open and persistent connections are simply an "
"OS function."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260420-01.en.xhtml:215
msgid ""
"These examples show the same pattern: Apple defines the scope narrowly "
"enough to preserve its own product design choices, then treats those same "
"choices as evidence that interoperability is unnecessary."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><h3>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260420-01.en.xhtml:220
msgid "Why does this matter for Free Software developers?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260420-01.en.xhtml:222
msgid ""
"The burden of requesting and eventually getting access to interoperability "
"rights falls almost entirely on developers. Under Apple’s model, they must "
"prove case by case that a feature is “used by Apple” before they can gain "
"access, while Apple remains free to reject the request based on its own "
"interpretation of the scope. The EC’s framework imposes on Apple "
"transparency obligations. For Free Software projects, this means technical "
"work becomes entangled with legal argument, procedural deadlines, and "
"repeated submissions."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260420-01.en.xhtml:231
msgid ""
"The mandatory developer fee adds to the problem. Article 6(7)  requires "
"interoperability to be free of charge, yet Apple still requires a paid "
"developer account to submit a request, which creates a financial hurdle at "
"the very point where the law is supposed to lower barriers. For volunteers, "
"small teams, and independent projects, that is not a minor inconvenience; it "
"is a structural filter on who can participate from the beginning."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><h3>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260420-01.en.xhtml:240
msgid "What effective interoperability needs"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260420-01.en.xhtml:242
msgid ""
"In the short term, effective and free interoperability access is essential "
"to a developer-friendly enforcement of the DMA. Equal and fair access for "
"all developers cannot depend solely on discretionary control of gatekeepers."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260420-01.en.xhtml:247
msgid ""
"Looking further ahead, shared governance is essential. Regulators alone "
"cannot ensure that interoperability serves the public interest; developers, "
"users, and civil society must have a genuine voice in how it is designed, "
"monitored, and enforced. The Free Software tradition, built on open "
"standards and community oversight, demonstrates that interoperability can be "
"democratically governed as a digital common, rather than shaped by bilateral "
"deals between gatekeepers and their largest competitors. That is the "
"standard the DMA should be held to."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><h3>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260420-01.en.xhtml:257
msgid "Call to action"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260420-01.en.xhtml:259
msgid ""
"The FSFE is still collecting first-hand accounts from developers who have "
"engaged with Apple’s interoperability process under Article 6(7), or who "
"were discouraged before they even began. Those experiences help document how "
"the process works in practice and provide concrete evidence for regulators "
"and enforcement actions."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260420-01.en.xhtml:265
msgid ""
"If you are a developer who has requested access to software or hardware "
"features under Article 6(7) of the DMA, or if you have considered doing so "
"but were discouraged by the process, the FSFE wants to hear from you. Your "
"experience can help document how interoperability works in practice and "
"support better enforcement."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260420-01.en.xhtml:272
msgid "Share your experience:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260420-01.en.xhtml:273
msgid ""
"<a class=\"btn btn-default\" href=\"https://survey.fsfe.org/index.php/"
"699938\">Start the survey</a>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><h3>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260420-01.en.xhtml:277
msgid "Support our work"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260420-01.en.xhtml:279
msgid ""
"Monitoring gatekeepers, analysing regulatory processes, and defending "
"software freedom takes independent resources. Your support helps the FSFE "
"continue this work, bring evidence to regulators, and push for "
"interoperability by design."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/2026/news-20260420-01.en.xhtml:284
msgid ""
"Please consider making a donation to support the FSFE’s work for Free "
"Software, Device Neutrality, and user choice."
msgstr ""

