msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><ul><li>
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202602.en.xhtml:201
msgid ""
"Show your gratitude: Think of a Free Software project you appreciate and "
"reach out to the maintainers. Say thank you using our <a href=\"https://"
"sharepic.fsfe.org/#ilovefs\">sharepic</a>, <a href=\"/contribute/"
"spreadtheword#ilovefs\">stickers, balloons</a>, <a href=\"/activities/"
"ilovefs/artwork/artwork.html\">artwork</a>, or <a href=\"/order/"
"order.html\">merchandise </a>for #ilovefs."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><ul><li>
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202602.en.xhtml:209
msgid ""
"Spread the love on social media: Share your appreciation with #ilovefs, "
"write a blog post, post pictures or <a href=\"https://media.fsfe.org/w/p/"
"u3Ep8hRP5vFdbgUE9LKScW\">video messages</a>, or send your thanks directly to "
"Free Software developers and contributors."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><ul><li>
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202602.en.xhtml:214
msgid ""
"Take action: Talking is silver, contributing is gold! Help a Free Software "
"project by donating, translating, or assisting its users. You can also "
"support our work with <a href=\"/donate/donate.html\">a donation to the FSFE."
"</a>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202602.en.xhtml:221
msgid ""
"We want to send a huge THANK YOU to everyone supporting us, including our "
"amazing donors! We may be behind the wheel, but you are the ones keeping us "
"moving forward. You can also <a href=\"/donate/donate.html\">support us</a>, "
"<a href=\"/contribute/contribute.html\">contribute to our work</a>, and <a "
"href=\"/about/groups.html\">join our community</a>. Are you using social "
"media? If so, do not forget to follow us there! You can also follow the FSFE "
"news in your <a href=\"/news/news.rss\">RSS Reader</a>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><h1>
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202603.en.xhtml:6 fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202603.en.xhtml:11
msgid "It's all about our community"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202603.en.xhtml:13
msgid ""
"Our March newsletter brings you the energy of 22 I Love Free Software Day "
"celebrations across Europe, the Norwegian release of Ada &amp; Zangemann, "
"updates on the Cyber Resilience Act and Router Freedom, and two fresh "
"Software Freedom Podcast episodes."
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'alt' of: <html><body><figure><img>
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202603.en.xhtml:20
msgid ""
"Graphic for the FSFE newsletter with the FSFE logo, a nI Love Free Software "
"collage that includes thank you cards, comic panels, a group photo and on "
"the bottom, a picture with books of Ada and Zangemann and the Router Freedom "
"icon"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202603.en.xhtml:23
msgid ""
"Spring is just around the corner, and we are feeling re-energised, not only "
"thanks to the sunshine, but also because of the inspiring days we spent "
"celebrating I Love Free Software Day across Europe. This year, 22 gatherings "
"took place in 12 European countries!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><h3>
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202603.en.xhtml:28
msgid "I Love Free Software Day 2026"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202603.en.xhtml:29
msgid ""
"Every year on 14 February and in the days around it, we come together, "
"online and in person, to express our appreciation to everyone who is part of "
"the Free Software communities. Whether through local meet-ups, talks, "
"workshops, postcards, blog posts, social media messages, or simple words of "
"gratitude, the message is clear: Free Software exists and thrives because of "
"the people who build, maintain, document, translate, test, and support it."
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'alt' of: <html><body><figure><img>
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202603.en.xhtml:39
msgid ""
"Two people standing inside a large red heart-shaped decoration in a public "
"indoor space"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202603.en.xhtml:43
msgid ""
"For the 2026 celebration, and under the motto \"Maintainers Matter\", our "
"communities organised 22 events across 12 different European countries, "
"reaching more than 300 people offline. And many more people celebrated it "
"online. Hundreds of individuals and organisations joined the celebration on "
"the Fediverse, sharing appreciation posts and gratitude messages. For the "
"first time, the celebration also reached the front page of Hacker News, "
"thanks to a \"Thank You\" blog post by Matthias Kirschner, the President of "
"the FSFE, <a href=\"https://k7r.eu/i-love-the-work-of-the-archwiki-"
"maintainers/\">who shared his appreciation for Arch Linux and the extensive "
"ArchWiki</a>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'alt' of: <html><body><figure><img>
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202603.en.xhtml:57
msgid ""
"Map showing locations in Europe with red heart markers representing events "
"for I Love Free Software Day 2026. Central text explains why we celebrate "
"this day."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202603.en.xhtml:61
msgid ""
"Besides, we had a special Software Freedom Podcast episode to mark this "
"special day with something nice. For our I Love Free Software Day podcast "
"episode <a href=\"/news/podcast/2026/episode-47.html\">we spoke with Lorenz "
"Kästle from the monitoring plugins</a>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><h3>
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202603.en.xhtml:65
msgid "DMA, CRA and Router Freedom"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202603.en.xhtml:66
msgid ""
"That was not the only podcast episode published in recent weeks. Remember "
"FOSDEM? Our 46th episode, recorded there, is now out! In it, Lucas Lasota "
"and Bonnie Mehring discuss <a href=\"/news/podcast/2026/"
"episode-46.html\">interoperability compliance under the EU's Digital Markets "
"Act (DMA) and mobile phones</a>. The episode dives deeper into compliance "
"changes in the Android Open Source Project (AOSP)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202603.en.xhtml:73
msgid ""
"During FOSDEM 2026, we also held a Q&amp;A session on the Cyber Resilience "
"Act, together with a representative of the German market surveillance "
"authority and the European Commission, as there are still uncertainties and "
"recurring questions. There, we talked about the role of the steward as "
"people are still unsure whether and under what circumstances they should or "
"might want to become a steward. <a href=\"/news/2026/"
"news-20260224-01.html\">One part of the question is relatively easy to "
"answer: no one has to become a steward. </a>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202603.en.xhtml:83
msgid ""
"Besides the option of becoming a steward, there is also the option of "
"attestation (Art. 25 CRA). In order to facilitate the due diligence "
"obligation, voluntary security attestation programmes could be established. "
"As uncertainty around attestation remains, <a href=\"https://dialog-"
"cybersicherheit.limesurvey.net/113884\">we launched a survey</a> to gather "
"input from the community. The survey closed at the end of February, and we "
"are currently evaluating the results. We will share the findings with "
"decision-makers and relevant stakeholders, incorporating them into the "
"ongoing process. As always, our focus is on ensuring that Free Software "
"contributors and small projects are protected and supported."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202603.en.xhtml:94
msgid ""
"The protection of Router Freedom in Europe is another topic that has kept us "
"busy in recent weeks. The European Union is about to reform the telecom "
"sector with the proposed Digital Networks Act (DNA). <a href=\"/news/2026/"
"news-20260218-01.html\">The position of the FSFE is that the Digital "
"Networks Act must move beyond fragmented national rules and establish a "
"clear, operational framework ensuring effective and uniform protection of "
"Router Freedom</a>. This requires setting a harmonised default across the EU "
"that properly reflects the interests of end-users and consumers. Any "
"deviation due to network topology should remain the exception, not the rule, "
"and must be transparently justified."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><h3>
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202603.en.xhtml:106
msgid "Keep Android Open"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202603.en.xhtml:107
msgid ""
"Together with other civil society organisations, the FSFE signed an open "
"letter addressed to Sundar Pichai, CEO of Google, regarding Google's "
"announced policy requiring all Android app developers to register centrally "
"with Google to be allowed to distribute applications outside the Google Play "
"Store. Google's plan would mean that all personal data of Free Software app "
"developers on Android would end up with Google, even apps distributed "
"outside the Play Store, by forcing developers to register and hand over ID. "
"It raises barriers for small and volunteer projects, like F-Droid, and "
"increases the risk of surveillance, censorship, and arbitrary bans against "
"privacy‑protecting and critical apps. The letter asks Google to rescind the "
"mandatory developer registration for all third-party distribution, engage in "
"transparent dialogue with civil society, Free Software communities, and "
"regulators on improving security without sacrificing openness, and commit to "
"platform neutrality so that Google's role as Android steward does not "
"conflict with its commercial interests."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202603.en.xhtml:123
msgid ""
"To help us, you can read and share the open letter: <a href=\"https://"
"keepandroidopen.org/open-letter/\">https://keepandroidopen.org/open-letter/</"
"a>.  If you are part of an organisation, join the signatories from across "
"civil society, Free Software communities, and industry."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202603.en.xhtml:127
msgid ""
"Please help so that Google also understands it is not in its interest to "
"jeopardise its own success in mobile by making Android unfriendly to "
"developers who care about software freedom"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><h3>
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202603.en.xhtml:131
msgid "From Ada's workshop"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202603.en.xhtml:132
msgid ""
"All these efforts, from policy and surveys to community celebrations and our "
"podcast, share a common goal: empowering people to understand, use, share, "
"and improve technology. This is exactly why stories like <a href=\"https://"
"ada.fsfe.org\">Ada &amp; Zangemann</a> matter so much. When Petter "
"discovered the book, he immediately felt that Norwegian-speaking readers "
"should have access to its inspiring message. Now, <em>Ada og Zangemann – En "
"fortelling om programvare, rullebrett og bringebæris</em> has been published "
"and was presented during the Norwegian I Love Free Software Day celebrations."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202603.en.xhtml:140
msgid ""
"Meanwhile, our community continues to organise events for children to learn "
"about Free Software with the help of Ada. At the beginning of February, at "
"the Kids Village Open Source event in Brussels, an Ada &amp; Zangemann "
"reading session in French took place alongside a small Ada-themed game."
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'alt' of: <html><body><figure><img>
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202603.en.xhtml:148
msgid ""
"Children and adults sit on a carpeted floor, engaging in a card game with "
"the illustrations from Ada and Zangemann. Nearby are balloons, chairs, and "
"plants."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202603.en.xhtml:152
msgid ""
"Last but not least, if you are in Germany and coming to <a href=\"/events/"
"index.html#event-20260328-01\">Chemnitzer Linux-Tage 2026</a>, come by to "
"say \"Hi!\" We will be there with a booth full of info material and "
"merchandise as well as giving some talks!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><h3>
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202603.en.xhtml:157
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202604.en.xhtml:92
msgid "Your support helps us move our work forward."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202603.en.xhtml:157
msgid ""
"We may be behind the wheel, but you are the ones keeping us moving forward. "
"We would like to thank our community and all the volunteers, supporters, and "
"donors who make our work possible, with a special mention to our translators "
"who make it possible for you to read this newsletter in your mother tongue."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202603.en.xhtml:162
msgid ""
"You can also <a href=\"/donate/donate.html\">support us</a>, <a href=\"/"
"contribute/contribute.html\">contribute to our work</a>, and <a href=\"/"
"about/groups.html\">join our community</a>. Are you using social media? If "
"so, do not forget to follow us there! You can also follow the FSFE news in "
"your <a href=\"/news/news.rss\">RSS Reader</a>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'alt' of: <html><image>
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202603.en.xhtml:189
msgid ""
"Graphic for the FSFE newsletter with the FSFE logo, a I Love Free Software "
"collage that includes thank you cards, comic panels, a group photo and on "
"the bottom, a picture with books of Ada and Zangemann and the Router Freedom "
"icon"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><h1>
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202604.en.xhtml:6 fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202604.en.xhtml:12
msgid "Full speed into conference season with a heartfelt “Thank you”"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202604.en.xhtml:14
msgid ""
"Conference season is in full swing! In the last week we have been navigating "
"the challenge of our payment provider ending our contract, attending events, "
"and preparing for what’s ahead. Check out our first interview on the 2026 "
"ilovefs celebrations and our two latest podcast episodes. Thank you to "
"everyone who supported us during this time of financial uncertainty!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'alt' of: <html><image>
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202604.en.xhtml:23
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202604.en.xhtml:118
msgid ""
"A collage featuring the FSFE logo, the Software Freedom podcast logo, binary "
"code forming a heart shape, and a hand holding a CANCELLED sign near a "
"laptop."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202604.en.xhtml:26
msgid ""
"Over the past weeks we have been very busy as<a href=\"/news/2026/"
"news-20260316-01.html\"> our long-term payment provider, Nexi, terminated "
"our contract without prior notice</a>. As a result, more than 450 current "
"FSFE supporters who rely in their regular donation to the FSFE on automatic "
"renewals via credit card or direct debit have been affected. While we had "
"already begun preparing a transition to a new payment provider, existing "
"supporter accounts unfortunately cannot be migrated automatically."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202604.en.xhtml:34
msgid ""
"Your response to our call for help has been truly incredible. We are deeply "
"grateful for our strong and supportive community: both for sharing our "
"message and for stepping in with financial support when it was most needed. "
"Thank you for helping us navigate this unexpected financial challenge!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><h3>
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202604.en.xhtml:40
msgid "Interoperability, Policy and Local Groups"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202604.en.xhtml:41
msgid ""
"A few weeks ago, our team contributed to a consultation by the UK "
"Competition and Markets Authority (CMA) on interoperability under the "
"Digital Markets, Competition and Consumers Act (DMCCA). In our response, we "
"urged the CMA to reject Apple’s voluntary interoperability commitments and "
"instead impose binding, interoperability-by-design obligations that protect "
"software freedom, consumer choice, and fair competition. You can read the "
"full response <a href=\"https://download.fsfe.org/campaigns/device-"
"neutrality/2026-03-FSFE-CMA-DMCCA-interop.pdf\">here</a>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202604.en.xhtml:49
msgid ""
"We also have two new episodes of our Software Freedom Podcast for you: <a "
"href=\"/news/podcast/2026/episode-49.html\">in episode 49, we speak with a "
"member of our local group in Zurich</a>, offering insights into their work, "
"local engagement, and the importance of community-driven initiatives in "
"advancing Software Freedom."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202604.en.xhtml:54
msgid ""
"In episode 48, <a href=\"/news/podcast/2026/episode-48.html\">we took a "
"closer look at the Cyber Resilience Act (CRA)</a>, addressing open questions "
"and ongoing discussions, such as attestation and what these regulatory "
"changes could mean for Free Software."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><h3>
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202604.en.xhtml:60
msgid "Reviving I love FS celebration and at the booth around Europe"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202604.en.xhtml:61
msgid ""
"Not long ago, the Free Software community celebrated “I Love Free Software "
"Day” : a day when the FSFE, our volunteers, and many other organisations and "
"individuals come together to thank all contributors for their dedication to "
"using, studying, sharing, and improving Free Software. We are starting to "
"revisit that special occasion with an interview featuring a volunteer from "
"Poznań, who organized a local event there, the most attended one in 2026!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202604.en.xhtml:69
msgid ""
"Besides, over the past weeks, we have been actively participating in events "
"across Europe. At the Chemnitzer Linux-Tage 2026 in Chemnitz, Germany (one "
"of the country’s largest and longest-running conferences dedicated to Free "
"Software), we had the opportunity to meet community members, exchange ideas, "
"and engage with a diverse audience through workshops, talks, and "
"discussions. Together with some of our German volunteers, we were present "
"with a booth and contributed a talk sharing practical insights on Free "
"Software licensing with developers."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202604.en.xhtml:79
msgid ""
"Also in Germany, we joined the 26th Gautinger Internet Meeting, where we "
"contributed to discussions on digital sovereignty. There we presented our "
"youth activities, including Youth Hacking for Freedom and the well-known "
"children’s book “Ada &amp; Zangemann”, highlighting the importance of "
"empowering young people to keep their curiosity and to understand and shape "
"technology to achieve digital sovereignty."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202604.en.xhtml:86
msgid ""
"And last but not least, we took part in the panel discussion “What does "
"Digital Sovereignty mean for Civil Society?”, organised by the ISOC "
"Switzerland Chapter in Zurich, Switzerland. The discussion highlighted the "
"crucial role that civil society plays in shaping a sovereign and sustainable "
"digital future."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202604.en.xhtml:93
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202605.en.xhtml:140
msgid ""
"We may be behind the wheel, but you’re the ones keeping us moving forward. "
"You can also <a href=\"/donate/donate.html\">support us</a>, <a href=\"/"
"contribute/contribute.html\">contribute to our work</a>, and <a href=\"/"
"about/groups.html\">join our community</a>. Are you using social media? If "
"so, do not forget to follow us there! You can also follow the FSFE news in "
"your <a href=\"/news/news.rss\">RSS Reader</a>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><h1>
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202605.en.xhtml:6 fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202605.en.xhtml:11
msgid ""
"Decades-long victory, bold Apple survey findings, legal workshop success "
"&amp; our 50th podcast episode"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202605.en.xhtml:13
msgid ""
"April brought LLW, where we gathered with Legal Network members to discuss a "
"wide range of legal and licensing topics. One of them was the DMA, "
"legislation that is keeping us busy: we are exposing how Apple keeps "
"blocking third-party developers, denying their interoperability requests. On "
"a brighter note, over ten years of advocacy paid off: the EC is protecting "
"users' right to install any software on radio devices.  And we reached "
"episode 50 in our SFP!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'alt' of: <html><image>
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202605.en.xhtml:23
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202605.en.xhtml:163
msgid ""
"Collage featuring the FSFE logo, an illustration of an open birdcage with "
"tech devices, a group photo at a LLW conference, and the Ada character on "
"roller skates."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><blockquote>
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202605.en.xhtml:27
msgid ""
"\"I spent all of my training budget this year on coming to LLW, but just the "
"networking itself has already paid off!\" <cite>LLW 2026 participant</cite>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><h3>
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202605.en.xhtml:32
msgid "European policy news: RED and DMA interoperability"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202605.en.xhtml:34
msgid ""
"We are starting this new month with great news: after more than ten years of "
"persistent advocacy, we have a significant win to celebrate.  The European "
"Commission has decided to protect users' right to install any software on "
"their radio devices, <a href=\"/news/2026/news-20260430-01.html\">abandoning "
"the article in the Radio Equipment Directive that threatened to undermine "
"this freedom</a>. This decision shows that persistent, evidence-based "
"engagement with EU policy processes can achieve, and protect, software "
"freedom. But this is also only possible when we have the long-term resources "
"and stability to stay in the room, follow the process, and act at the right "
"moment. That is exactly <a href=\"/donate/donate.html\">why we need your "
"continued support</a>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202605.en.xhtml:47
msgid ""
"Meanwhile, we have monitored how<a href=\"/news/2026/"
"news-20260420-01.html\"> Apple is implementing its interoperability "
"obligations under the DMA</a>. Our recently released report <a "
"href=\"https://download.fsfe.org/campaigns/device-neutrality/FSFE-DMA-"
"AppleReport-v1.pdf\">“The challenges of regulating interoperability: "
"Analysing Apple’s request-based approach under the Digital Markets Act”</a> "
"sheds light on how Apple has handled those requests in practice. Our "
"analysis shows how 56 interoperability requests under the Digital Markets "
"Act have produced no concrete solutions by Apple, and how their refusals "
"contradict their own official documentation, leaving third-party developers "
"locked out of iOS and iPadOS, despite the European Commission’s latest "
"specification decision."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202605.en.xhtml:60
msgid ""
"Following our publication, we published a <a href=\"https://"
"background.tagesspiegel.de/digitalisierung-und-ki/briefing/wird-europa-seine-"
"eigenen-regeln-durchsetzen\">summary of the report in the Tagesspiegel "
"Background (DE)</a>. In the contribution, we explain how interoperability "
"can be a powerful tool to break tech monopolies in the mobile market, and "
"how its enforcement in the DMA is needed to empower Free Software developers."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><h3>
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202605.en.xhtml:67
msgid "Software Freedom Podcast: episode 50 about NGI"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202605.en.xhtml:68
msgid ""
"And more European news! Did you know that the FSFE is a partner of the "
"European initiative Next Generation Internet Zero? Under this umbrella, the "
"FSFE supports NGI0 grantee projects on legal and licensing issues, as well "
"as helping them to become REUSE compliant. Although this project is ending "
"next year, we are also happy to announce the new initiative that will follow "
"in its steps: the EU project Restack. Listen to the <a href=\"/news/podcast/"
"2026/episode-50.html\">latest episode of our podcast </a>in which Bonnie and "
"Gabriel discuss NGI0, introduce Restack, and explain why we need sustainable "
"long term funding for fostering the Free Software ecosystem. If you know a "
"Free Software project, or you have an idea that can contribute to an open, "
"resilient, trustworthy, sustainable, and human-centered internet, you can "
"apply for NGI0 funding:<a href=\"https://nlnet.nl/funding.html\">https://"
"nlnet.nl/funding.html</a>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202605.en.xhtml:84
msgid ""
"By the way, this is episode 50 of our podcast! We want to take a moment to "
"thank every single one of you on the other side, listening to the Software "
"Freedom Podcast. Fifty episodes in, and it is your curiosity, your support, "
"and your commitment to software freedom that keep this going. We are truly "
"grateful to our community and our listeners! And if you are a newcomer, <a "
"href=\" /news/podcast.html\">you can find all our episodes here</a>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><h3>
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202605.en.xhtml:92
msgid "From the stages: LLW and more!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202605.en.xhtml:93
msgid ""
"But that is not all that has happened in the last weeks! A few weeks ago <a "
"href=\"/news/2026/news-20260427-01.html\">the Free Software Legal &amp; "
"Licensing Workshop 2026 took place in Berlin,</a> bringing together over 100 "
"legal and compliance professionals, technologists, and policy experts from "
"all over the globe. The LLW, organised by the FSFE, continued to explore the "
"evolving legal landscapes impacting Free Software, with many discussions "
"focusing on how software licensing is impacted by the advent of large "
"language models and AI. Ths event was, once again, possible thanks to our "
"2026 sponsors: our Diamond sponsors Mercedes and Red Hat; the Sapphire "
"sponsors Amazon (AWS), Microsoft, and Siemens; Topaz sponsors Bosch, "
"Ericsson, and Google; and our Ruby sponsors Bird &amp; Bird, Eclipse "
"Foundation, and Liferay."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202605.en.xhtml:107
msgid ""
"Not only at LLW did we learn about legal topics. Check out our <a "
"href=\"https://mastodon.social/@fsfe\">Mastodon handle</a>, where we "
"regularly post poll questions on legal topics. They can come in handy in "
"unexpected places: thanks to one of those polls, this editor actually knew "
"an answer at the Pub Quiz during OggCamp 2026!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202605.en.xhtml:113
msgid ""
"Speaking of which, these past weeks have been busy on the events front. "
"After seven years, we were thrilled to return to OggCamp, where we ran an "
"information booth and gave presentations. We also attended FOSS North, and "
"last weekend joined the Augsburger Linux Info Day, where we delivered a "
"keynote and a workshop."
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'alt' of: <html><body><figure><img>
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202605.en.xhtml:121
msgid ""
"A booth with FSFE diverse information material with two women standing "
"behind it"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202605.en.xhtml:125
msgid ""
"In the coming weeks, our volunteers will be at the Festival de Tecnologia "
"Popular de Setúbal, the Tübingen Digital Freedom Days, and more! Check <a "
"href=\"events/events.html\">events.fsfe.org</a>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><h3>
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202605.en.xhtml:129
msgid "From the Ada workshop"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202605.en.xhtml:131
msgid ""
"The illustrated story of ‘Ada &amp; Zangemann’ continues reaching kids (and "
"adults) worldwide. Recently, the Austrian Ministry of Education released <a "
"href=\"https://www.eduvidual.at/course/view.php?id=218862\">an online course "
"about ‘Ada &amp; Zangemann’</a> with really cool exercises (and for students "
"of German it can also be a great way to practice their German skills with "
"Ada)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><h3>
#: fsfe.org/news/nl/nl-202605.en.xhtml:139
msgid "Your support helps us move our work forward"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><h1>
