#: fsfe.org/news/podcast/transcript/2026/episode-44.en.xhtml:9
msgid "SFP#44: Policy and EU: Navigate through current relevant EU initiatives"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/podcast/2026/episode-44.en.xhtml:12
msgid ""
"January is a busy month. We all come back from our relaxing (or in some "
"cases rather stressful) holidays and what best to do with all the energy the "
"New Year brings along? Of course, we have to advocate for Free Software! One "
"way is advocating for the representation of Free Software in the initiatives "
"the European Union is working."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/podcast/2026/episode-44.en.xhtml:20
msgid ""
"In our first Software Freedom Podcast episode of the year, Alex and Bonnie "
"talk about the \"Digital Decade policy program\", the \"European Open "
"Digital Ecosystem\" and the Procurement initiative that are open for "
"consultation and awaiting your feedback. Alex and Bonnie help you to "
"navigate the European politics."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><p>
#: fsfe.org/news/podcast/2026/episode-44.en.xhtml:26
msgid ""
"The FSFE's policy work is an important part of our aim to safeguard Free "
"Software and help to further the implementation of \"Public Money? Public "
"Code!\". You can support our work by"
